				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$L$\end{document} and in association with substorm injections, dipolarizations, and other nightside phenomena. Turner et al. (2017b) used MagEIS data along with numerous other in-situ measurements to examine a complex series of injections observed during a relatively quiet interval (maximum AE<300nT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
