				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$L$\end{document}, MLT, and time. They demonstrated that at least 5 of the observed injections were localized (narrow) in MLT, while one large scale injection was also observed across the entire nightside. These results concerning the scale size of the injection region are important towards quantifying the role that injections of seed electrons contribute to the overall formation of the MeV radiation belt.

MagEIS measurements have also provided important information on the global, energy-dependent radiation belt response to different interplanetary drivers. For example, Shen et al. (2017) examined the influence of coronal mass ejections (CMEs) and stream interaction regions (SIRs) on the outer radiation belt and found that CME driving was more effective at enhancing the belts at lower L\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
