Of course, radiation belt enhancements cannot be studied without a careful consideration of the loss processes that influence the rate and extent of electron enhancement. The Van Allen Probes have shed considerable light on this topic and there is now strong evidence that the large scale, rapid flux dropouts observed at higher L\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
