The primary data product from the HIGH unit ion telescopes was the main rate, similar to the electron main rates. Here, an ion main rate LUT was used to define 32 main channels across the three detectors. In all of the ion MR LUTs used on orbit, the first 21 channels were obtained from the front (MPA) detectors, providing ∼60keV–1MeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
