Figures are provided in the Electronic Supplementary Material that summarize the noise and detection-efficiency signatures in the MagEIS proton data from the MPA detectors. In general, the proton data from the MPA detectors should only be used qualitatively and with extreme care, and only until mid-2013. We recommend using RBSPICE proton measurements instead, which nominally cover the same energy range (∼60keV–1MeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
